  "Sanction Details" : "SEC LITIGATION RELEASE NO. 19739 / JUNE 23, 2006; ON JUNE 19, 2006, A U. S. DISTRICT JUDGE FOR THE DISTRICT OF MASSACHUSETTS, ENTERED A DEFAULT JUDGMENT AS TO DEFENDANT T. GENE GILMAN AND OTHERS. THE ORDER RESTRAINED AND ENJOINED THE HIM FROM FUTURE VIOLATIONS OF SECTION 17(A) OF THE SECURITIES ACT OF 1933, SECTION 10(B) OF THE SECURITIES EXCHANGE ACT OF 1934 (\"EXCHANGE ACT\"), AND RULE 10B-5 THEREUNDER. THE ORDER ENJOINED HIM FROM AIDING AND ABETTING VIOLATIONS OF SECTIONS 15(A) AND 15(C) OF THE EXCHANGE ACT AND SECTIONS 206(1) AND 206(2) OF THE INVESTMENT ADVISERS ACT OF 1940 (\"ADVISERS ACT\"). THE COURT ORDERED THE DEFENDANTS TO PAY JOINT AND SEVERAL DISGORGEMENT AND PREJUDGMENT INTEREST IN THE RESPECTIVE AMOUNTS OF $14,000,000 AND $1,681,718.26. THE COURT IMPOSED CIVIL PENALTIES AGAINST GILMAN IN THE AMOUNT OF $100,000."
